===============================================================================
                    DUALARMCONTROL MC_RTC CONTROLLER DOCUMENTATION
===============================================================================


1. CONTROLLER ARCHITECTURE & LIFECYCLE
--------------------------------------
It uses a "Double-Pointer State Pattern" (via the transitionTo method) to eliminate memory allocation 
jitter inside the real-time control loop.

FSM State Flow:
[ entryStateIdle ] -------> [ entryStateIndependent ] ------> [ entryStateCollaborative ]
        |                              |                                |
        v                              v                                v
    stateIdle                  stateIndependent                stateCollaborative
(Holds for 3.0s)             (Moves to safe targets)         (Interpolates Virtual Object)


2. STATE MACHINE BREAKDOWN
--------------------------

A. IDLE STATE (entryStateIdle -> stateIdle)
* Behavior: Holds the initial posture of both robots for exactly 3.0 seconds 
 

B. COLLABORATIVE STATE (entryStateCollaborative -> stateCollaborative)
* Behavior:
  1. Virtual Frame Initialization: Computes the midpoint between the 
     two end-effectors to instantiate a virtual object frame (x_0_objectCurrent_).
  2. Rigid Offsets: Computes and locks the relative transformation offsets 
     (leftOffset_ and rightOffset_) from the object center to each end-effector.
  3. Path Interpolation: Linearly interpolates the virtual object frame towards 
     sequential targets at a constant velocity profile of 5 cm/s (0.05 m/s).

* Waypoints: 
  - Waypoint 1: [X: 0.50, Y: 0.25, Z: 0.09]
  - Waypoint 2: [X: 0.70, Y: 0.25, Z: 0.19] (Moves 20cm forward, 10cm up)


3. IMPEDANCE CONTROL CONFIGURATION
----------------------------------
6D Spatial Vectors ordered as: [Angular_X, Angular_Y, Angular_Z, Linear_X, Linear_Y, Linear_Z]

* Virtual Mass (massGains): Set to 1.0 Constant (kg / kg*m^2).
* Virtual Stiffness (springGains): Set to 200.0 Constant (N/m).
* Virtual Damping (damperGains): Analytically computed for critical damping 
  to prevent oscillations: D = 2 * sqrt(K * M).
* Feedforward Force Profile: The Left Arm impedance task is configured with 
  a constant downward target contact force of 25.0 N along the Linear Z-axis.

